Keep floating actor-name tooltips visible when the HUD is hidden.

OpenMW's "Hide UI" toggle sets mHudEnabled=false and, in
WindowManager::updateVisible(), hides both the HUD (mHud) and the entire
tooltip layer (mToolTips). The tooltip layer is what renders the floating
name shown above an NPC/creature when the player looks at it (the game-mode
branch of ToolTips::update() driven by mFocusObject). Hiding it means the
companion's second-screen crosshair has no on-world name to pair with while
Hide UI is active.

ToolTips::update() already hides all of its children each frame and only
re-shows the focus-object tooltip in game mode (or the hover tooltip in GUI
mode), so keeping the tooltip layer itself visible does not leak any other
HUD element. We therefore drop the mHudEnabled dependency for the tooltip
layer only; mHud stays gated by Hide UI exactly as before.

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -645,7 +645,9 @@
         if (!mMap)
             return; // UI not created yet

         mHud->setVisible(mHudEnabled && !loading);
-        mToolTips->setVisible(mHudEnabled && !loading);
+        // COMPANION: keep floating actor-name tooltips visible even when the HUD is
+        // hidden via the Hide UI toggle. update() only shows the focus-object name.
+        mToolTips->setVisible(!loading);

         bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();

